# Git and PR Governance

- Do not push directly to `main`; all changes must go through pull requests.
- Every pull request must reference an existing issue (for example: `Closes #123`).
- Keep PRs focused and reviewable; split unrelated changes into separate PRs.
- Include validation evidence in PRs (tests/lint/manual checks relevant to the change).
- Update `CHANGELOG.md` when behavior, contracts, or data model changes.
- For risky changes (migrations/scheduler/ingest semantics), include rollback notes in the PR.
- Owner/admin bypass is allowed only for exceptional emergencies and must be documented afterward.
